
---


@startuml
' Entities related to people
class Person {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

abstract class CreativeEmployee extends Person {}

class Director extends CreativeEmployee {
  - hasOscar: boolean
  - assistantName: String
}

class Actor extends CreativeEmployee {
  - hasOscar: boolean
  - education: String
}

class Technician extends Person {
  - fieldOfActivity: String
}

class Screenwriter {
  - name: String
  - mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  - title: String
  - version: String
  - date: Date
  - numberOfScenes: int
  - plot: String
}

class FilmSet {
  - location: String
}

class Film {
  - title: String
  - yearOfRelease: int
}

enum Genre {
  Thriller,
  Action,
  Horror,
  Comedy
}

class Novel {
  - title: String
  - author: String
}

' Relationships
Person <|-- CreativeEmployee
CreativeEmployee <|-- Director
CreativeEmployee <|-- Actor
CreativeEmployee <|-- Technician : is not, but grouped for clarity

Screenwriter "1" --> "many" Screenplay
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Film
Film "many" --> "many" FilmSet
Film "1" --> "1" Genre
Film "1" --> "1" Screenplay
Screenplay "0..1" --> "1" Novel
Screenplay "0..1" --> "1" Concept

Actor "many" --> "1" Film
Director "1" --> "1" Film
Technician "many" --> "1" Film

note right of Screenplay
  A screenplay can be based on either a novel or a concept.
end note

note left of Film
  A film uses multiple sets and belongs to one genre.
end note

@enduml

---

### 🧩 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Inheritance**: `CreativeEmployee` is an abstract base class for `Director`, `Actor`, and possibly `Technician` (though it's more accurate to treat `Technician` as separate).
- **Associations**:
  - A `Screenwriter` writes many `Screenplays`.
  - A `Film` uses multiple `FilmSets` and has one `Genre`.
  - A `Screenplay` is used by exactly one `Film`.
  - An `Actor` appears in a `Film`.
  - A `Director` directs a `Film`.
- **Concept vs Novel**: The `Screenplay` is associated with either a `Novel` or a `Concept`. Since "concept" isn't a defined class, we model this with an optional association.

